Parts of Ladysmith, in KwaZulu-Natal, remain flooded this morning. Search and rescue teams are continuing with their operations today. eNCA's Mawande Kheswa has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 LADYSMITH - Parts of Ladysmith, in KwaZulu-Natal, remain flooded on Tuesday morning. Search and rescue teams are continuing with their operations. READ: Relief efforts underway in Ladysmith At least one person has died and 70 more evacuated. There have been severe storms in the province over the past few weeks.